<div class="post-header mb2">
  <h2>A framework for non-expert robot programming facilitated by a self-localizing smart device</h2>
  <span class="post-meta">Jun 8, 2015</span><br>
  
  <span class="post-meta small">
  
    2 minute read
  
  </span>
</div>

<article class="post-content">
  <script type="text/javascript" src="http://cdn.mathjax.org/mathjax/latest/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS-MML_HTMLorMML"></script>

<p>This was my master thesis project at KUKA Roboter GmbH, Augsburg.The project has been finsihed in 6 months. For this project, I created requirement analysis, implemented algorithms <a href="http://docs.opencv.org/modules/imgproc/doc/feature_detection.html?highlight=houghcircles#houghcircles">Hough Circle</a> and <a href="http://pointclouds.org/documentation/tutorials/cylinder_segmentation.php">Cylinder Model Segmentation</a> using <a href="http://opencv.org/"> OpenCV</a> and <a href="http://pointclouds.org/">PCL</a> C++ libraries for the better performance, developed algorithms and implemented them in C++ on <a href="http://www.ros.org/">ROS</a> platform, Developed Java APIs to tech the LBR iiwa to pick-and-place the objects. </p>.   
</article>


  





